Package gov.nasa.jpl.aerie.merlin.timeline

Class SimulationTimeline<$Timeline>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nasa.jpl.aerie.merlin.timeline.SimulationTimeline<$Timeline>
  • Type Parameters:
    $Timeline - A phantom type parameter that distinguishes individual timeline instances.
    public final class SimulationTimeline<$Timeline>
extends Object
    A persistent representation of EffectExpressions.

    SimulationTimeline is an efficient implementation of EffectExpression that supports multiple simultaneous unterminated timelines. The equivalent of an EventGraph for SimulationTimelines is a History, which may be extended with events and evaluated against Projections.

    For efficiency, Projections may be registered with a SimulationTimeline so their results are cached and reused for later queries.

    The phantom type parameter T distinguishes one timeline from another, ensuring that time points and projectors related to one timeline cannot accidentally be used with another timeline. SimulationTimeline instances are instantiated with an unknown type for this type parameter, represented by the wildcard symbol <?>.

    See Also:
    Wikipedia: Persistent data structure, History, Query, EventGraph
